<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. C. Ren &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Lophiotremataceae" genus="Hermatomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hermatomyces jinghaensis" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jinghaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Hermatomyces jinghaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is introduced as a new species based on its distinct morphology and the phylogenetic results of a combined LSU, ITS, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">tub</emphasis>
2, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">tef</emphasis>
1-α and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">rpb</emphasis>
2 dataset. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. C. Ren &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Lophiotremataceae" genus="Hermatomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hermatomyces jinghaensis" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jinghaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Hermatomyces jinghaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nested with 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Hermatomycetaceae" genus="H." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="H. clematidis" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="clematidis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">H. clematidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Hermatomycetaceae" genus="H." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="H. trangensis" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="trangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">H. trangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a strongly supported monophyletic group (99% ML, 100% MP, 1.00 PP; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Phylogenetic RAxML tree based on analysis of a combined LSU, ITS, tub 2, tef 1 - α and rpb 2 and dataset. Bootstrap support values for ML and MP equal to or higher than 75 % and Bayesian PP equal to or greater than 0.95 are shown at nodes. Hyphens (--) represent support values less than 75 % / 0.95 BYPP. The ex-type strains are in bold and the new isolate in this study is in blue bold. The tree is rooted with Anteaglonium globosum (ANM 925.2) and A. parvulum (MFLUCC 14 - 0821). The scale bar represents the expected number of nucleotide substitutions per site." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.82.67973.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/575839" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">1</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. C. Ren &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Lophiotremataceae" genus="Hermatomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hermatomyces jinghaensis" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jinghaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Hermatomyces jinghaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by both lenticular and cylindrical conidia. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. C. Ren &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Lophiotremataceae" genus="Hermatomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hermatomyces jinghaensis" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jinghaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Hermatomyces jinghaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Hermatomycetaceae" genus="H." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="H. clematidis" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="clematidis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">H. clematidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having cylindrical conidia with one or two columns, each of which has 6-8 cells with large guttules, while the latter has 5-6 cells for each column conidia. 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Lophiotremataceae" genus="Hermatomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hermatomyces trangensis" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="trangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Hermatomyces trangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Hermatomycetaceae" genus="H." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="H. jinghaensis" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jinghaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">H. jinghaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having only lenticular conidia.
</paragraph>
